Source: libdbi
Section: libs
Priority: optional
Maintainer: David Parker <david@neongoat.com>
Standards-Version: 3.0.1

Package: libdbi-dev
Section: devel
Architecture: any
Depends: libdbi0 (= ${Source-Version}), libc6-dev
Description: Database independent abstraction layer for C (development files)
 The libdbi-dev package contains the header files, static libraries,
 and documentation needed to develop applications with libdbi.

Package: libdbi0
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}
Suggests: libdbd-mysql | libdbd-pgsql
Description: Database independent abstraction layer for C
 libdbi implements a database-independent abstraction layer in C, similar to the
 DBI/DBD layer in Perl. Writing one generic set of code, programmers can
 leverage the power of multiple databases and multiple simultaneous database
 connections by using this framework.

Package: libdbd-mysql
Architecture: any
Depends: libdbi0 (= ${Source-Version}), libmysqlclient6, zlib1g (>= 1:1.1.3)
Description: MySQL database server driver for libdbi
 This driver provides connectivity to MySQL database servers through the
 libdbi database independent abstraction layer. Switching a program's driver
 does not require recompilation or rewriting source code.

Package: libdbd-pgsql
Architecture: any
Depends: libdbi0 (= ${Source-Version}), libpgsql2 (>= 6.4-0), libpgsql2 (<< 7.0)
Description: PostgreSQL database server driver for libdbi
 This driver provides connectivity to PostgreSQL database servers through the
 libdbi database independent abstraction layer. Switching a program's driver
 does not require recompilation or rewriting source code.
